---
description: LLM template generation rules
globs:
  - "backend/src/services/llm/**"
  - "backend/src/routes/llm.ts"
  - "frontend/src/features/llm/**"
  - "shared/src/llm/**"
  - "shared/src/template/**"
---

LLM is a helper, not the source of truth. Generated content must be validated
before it becomes a saved template.

Rules:

- Keep llama.cpp behind an adapter/service.
- Do not hard-code the app to a single provider if a small adapter keeps it flexible.
- Always validate generated template JSON against shared schemas before saving.
- Keep deterministic fallback behavior when llama.cpp is unavailable.
- Do not let LLM failures break Templates page, Editor, or manual template creation.
- Keep prompts and response parsing close to the LLM service.
- Keep frontend LLM UI isolated under `frontend/src/features/llm/**`.
- Do not store raw unvalidated LLM output in `data/db.json`.
- Do not add cloud LLM dependencies unless Karen explicitly asks.

If changing the LLM response contract:

- update `shared/src/llm/schema.ts`;
- update backend validation;
- update frontend API/client code;
- mention the contract change in the PR;
- run `npm run typecheck` and `npm run build`.
